    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! \ud83d\ude97\u2728 You have to see this beauty in person\u2014it\u2019s in absolute showroom condition! I\u2019ve taken incredible care of it, and it honestly looks and drives like it just rolled off the lot. Not a single scratch, dent, or worry. If you\u2019re looking for a ride that\u2019s been totally babied and is ready for its next adventure, this is the one! Feel free to message me with any questions!",
      "price": 44500.0,
      "reputation": 0.5,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 21
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Offering a superlative 2004 BMW M3 (E46) in collector-grade condition. This specimen features the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six, characterized by its individual throttle bodies and a 8,000 RPM redline. The powertrain is mated to a precise Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory limited-slip differential. Mechanically, the vehicle is beyond reproach: the dual-VANOS system has been professionally serviced, and the rod bearings have been replaced as a preventative measure. The rear subframe\u2014a known point of deflection\u2014has been reinforced to ensure chassis rigidity. Every suspension bushing is tight, providing the telepathic steering response these cars are known for. The exterior retains its factory luster with perfect panel gaps and zero oxidation. This is a turn-key, investment-grade driver for the true enthusiast.",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 21
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "2021 Sedan. Mint condition. Garage kept. No accidents. Original paint. Clean title. Inspection welcome.",
      "price": 43500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
